    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-04-15T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-04-15T12:00:00-05:00" n="54"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d54">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/4–948: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State, at Bogotá</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-04-15T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 15, 1948—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Telmar</hi> 66. With reference to the last para of <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Martel</hi> 28 of Apr 7 and to <hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >Martel</hi> 36 of Apr 9, FE and S/P<note n="90" xml:id="d54fn90">Office of
                        Far Eastern Affairs and Policy Planning Staff, respectively.</note> are of
                    the opinion that it would be unwise at this time to reopen the question of
                    so-called short-term <pb facs="0066" n="56" xml:id="pg_56"/> assistance to
                    China, since the National Security Council has postponed indefinitely its
                    consideration of the problem.<note n="91" xml:id="d54fn91">At a meeting on April
                        2 the National Security Council agreed that NSC6 had been overtaken by
                        events and deferred further action on the subject of China pending receipt
                        of a position paper from the Department of State.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Unless you wish to press the Defense Establishment for clarification immediately,
                    Dept proposes to defer seeking suggested clarifications until it is prepared to
                    present basic paper on our position regarding China on which it is now
                    working.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
